title: $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/core-api-docs/readme

This plugin provides the human-readable reference documentation for core filter operators and widgets.

Canonical content lives under the plugin namespace:

* `$:/plugins/tiddlywiki/core-api-docs/filters/...`
* `$:/plugins/tiddlywiki/core-api-docs/widgets/...`

The tw5.com edition keeps the original document titles (e.g. ''contains Operator'', ''ActionNavigateWidget'') and transcludes these plugin tiddlers. This preserves wiki search/navigation behaviour while keeping the documentation source centralized in the plugin.

Structured metadata fields (such as `op-purpose`, `op-input`, widget attributes, etc.) live in the `core-api-attributes` plugin under the `$:/docs/` namespace, and are validated by `core-api-schema`.

Display templates/macros remain in the tw5.com edition. tw5.com pages consume `$:/docs/...` metadata so that site rendering and editor tooling share the same source of truth while prose content stays centralized in this plugin.
